# Technical Debt Tracker

## Overview

| Date | Objective | Outcome |
| ------ | ----------- | --------- |
| 2025-12-30 | Track and resolve all FIXME/TODO comments referencing closed issues | Created 8 category issues + 1 Epic, updated 20+ source files |

## When to Use

- Auditing codebase for FIXME/TODO comments referencing closed issues
- Creating structured issues for each debt category
- Updating stale issue references in source code

## Verified Workflow

```bash
# Discovery
grep -rn "FIXME\|TODO" --include="*.py" --include="*.mojo" --exclude-dir='.*' .
grep -oP "FIXME\(#\K\d+" --include="*.mojo" --exclude-dir='.*' -r . | sort -u
gh issue view <number> --json state -q '.state'

# Create issues (check labels first!)
gh label list --limit 50
gh issue create --title "[Category] Description" --body "..." --label "existing-label"

# Create Epic
gh issue create --title "[Epic] Technical Debt Resolution" --body "..."

# Bulk update references
# Use replace_all: true — FIXME(#OLD) -> FIXME(#NEW)

# Verify
grep -rn "#OLD_NUMBER" --include="*.mojo" --exclude-dir='.*' .
```

## Failed Attempts

| Attempt | What Was Tried | Why It Failed | Lesson Learned |
| --------- | ---------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| Use arbitrary label names | Created issues with labels not in repo | `gh issue create` fails: label not found | Run `gh label list --limit 50` first |
| N/A for others | Direct approach worked | N/A | Solution was straightforward |
